abstract: It is not the first time the impeachment managers have brought up the senator, who had been a fierce critic of the president.
snippet: It is not the first time the impeachment managers have brought up the senator, who had been a fierce critic of the president.
lead_paragraph: Representative Hakeem Jeffries, Democrat of New York and one of the impeachment managers, invoked Senator John McCain in his closing arguments in a subtle jab at President Trump, who has continued to nurse his grudge against the lawmaker even after his death.

abstract: The Arab League rejected U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan at a meeting of foreign ministers in Cairo on Saturday, saying it would not lead to a just peace deal.

abstract: The Palestinian Authority has cut all ties with the United States and Israel, including those relating to security, after rejecting a Middle East peace plan presented by U.S. President Donald Trump, Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas said on Saturday.

abstract: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said on Friday that a prospective visit by Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy to the White House was not conditional on Ukraine opening an investigation into the son of former Vice President Joe Biden.
snippet: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said on Friday that a prospective visit by Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy to the White House was not conditional on Ukraine opening an investigation into the son of former Vice President Joe Biden.
lead_paragraph: KIEV — U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said on Friday that a prospective visit by Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy to the White House was not conditional on Ukraine opening an investigation into the son of former Vice President Joe Biden.
headline_main: Pompeo Says Zelenskiy White House Visit Not Conditional on Biden Probes

abstract: Republicans have embraced the idea that the president acted inappropriately, but his actions did not warrant removal from office.
snippet: Republicans have embraced the idea that the president acted inappropriately, but his actions did not warrant removal from office.
lead_paragraph: Representative Hakeem Jeffries, Democrat of New York and one of the impeachment managers, sought to counter a growing argument among Republicans in the Senate: acknowledging that President Trump’s decision to withhold critical military aid as part of an effort to pressure Ukraine into investigating a political rival was not appropriate, but not to the level of removing him from office.
headline_main: If Trump is not removed, how can voters be sure the next election is fair, Jeffries asks.
